dialogue: We don’t need no room. My granddaddy used to take women on the backs of horses.
You sure is country. I didn’t know you was this country.
There’s a lot of things you don’t know about me. Come on, let me show you what this country boy can do.
Let’s go to my place. I got a room with a bed if Leroy don’t come back there.
Who’s Leroy? You ain’t said nothing about no Leroy.
He used to be my man. He ain’t coming back.
You let him have your key?
Did you let him have your key?
He got a key but he ain’t coming back.
